  "title": "Create carbon footprint reports via OData",
  "content": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><p>You may create an ITAM carbon footprint report via OData. The following example shows how to create a simple ITAM report.</p>\n<h2>Use case</h2>\n<p>Your organization wants to create an ITAM report that reflects the hardware usage emissions by asset model.</p>\n<p>To create the report via OData, perform the following steps.</p>\n<h3 id=\"Connect_to_the_OData_feed\">Connect to the OData feed</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Open Power BI Desktop. On the <strong>Home</strong> page, select <strong>Get data</strong> &gt; <strong>OData feed</strong>.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/4/4a/SMAXBIODataCase1.png\" title=\"/file/images/4/4a/SMAXBIODataCase1.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCase1.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4a/SMAXBIODataCase1.png\" height=\"527\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCase1_e3f53335.png\" style=\"width:230px;height:527px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"230\"/> </a></li>\n<li>In the <strong>OData feed</strong> window, input your OData feed URL in the <strong>URL</strong> field, and click <strong>OK</strong>.<br/>\n<code>https://<em>&lt;Service Management host name&gt;</em>:<em>&lt;port number&gt;</em>/datahub/<em>&lt;tenant ID&gt;</em>/odata/</code> or <code>https://<em>&lt;Service Management host name&gt;</em>:<em>&lt;port number&gt;</em>/datahub/<em>&lt;tenant ID&gt;</em>/odata</code><br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/0/0b/SMAXBIODataCase2.png\" title=\"/file/images/0/0b/SMAXBIODataCase2.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCase2.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/0/0b/SMAXBIODataCase2.png\" height=\"177\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCase2_66579658.png\" style=\"width:554px;height:177px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"554\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Power BI Desktop prompts you to enter your credentials. Select <strong>Basic</strong> and input your user name and password, and then click <strong>Save</strong>. See <a href=\"/doc/423/26.1/useodataforbiintegration#Authentication_method\" title=\"Authentication method\">Authentication method</a> for detailed information.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/f/f0/SMAXBIODataCase3.png\" title=\"/file/images/f/f0/SMAXBIODataCase3.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCase3.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/f/f0/SMAXBIODataCase3.png\" height=\"238\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCase3_84288942.png\" style=\"width:554px;height:238px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"554\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Now, you can connect to the Service Management data. Power BI Desktop displays the available tables and other data elements in the <strong>Navigator</strong> window.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/4/43/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport1.png\" title=\"/file/images/4/43/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport1.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport1.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/43/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport1.png\" height=\"738\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport1_8228743f.png\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 738px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"800\"/> </a></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Sort out the data</h3>\n<p>To create a report that reflects the hardware usage emissions by asset model, you need to import and sort out the data of <b>AssetModel</b> and <strong>Device</strong>.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Select <b>AssetModel</b> and <strong>Device</strong> from the <strong>Navigator</strong> list, and then click <strong>Load</strong>.</li>\n<li>After you select <strong>Load</strong>, Power BI Desktop imports the data, and may display a <strong>Load</strong> window of the import progress.</li>\n<li>Once complete, Power BI Desktop displays the available data in the side panel.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/d/d5/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport2.png\" title=\"/file/images/d/d5/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport2.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport2.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/d/d5/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport2.png\" height=\"800\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport2_2b610195.png\" style=\"width: 613.881px; height: 800px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"613.880742913001\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Select the <strong>Table </strong>type in the <strong>Visualizations </strong>panel.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/8/8b/SMAXBIODataCase6.png\" title=\"/file/images/8/8b/SMAXBIODataCase6.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCase6.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/8/8b/SMAXBIODataCase6.png\" height=\"314\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCase6_dfc78945.png\" style=\"width:182px;height:314px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"182\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Expand the Device file, and then select the <strong>AssetModel </strong>and <b>LifetimeUsageEmissions </b>fields, which are required for creating this report.<br/>\n\tNow you can see the following table in the UI:<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/4/4b/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport3.png\" title=\"/file/images/4/4b/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport3.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport3.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4b/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport3.png\" height=\"248\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport3_10d7738d.png\" style=\"width:300px;height:248px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"300\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Go to <strong>Modeling</strong> &gt; <strong>Manage relationships</strong>. You can see the relationship between <strong>Device </strong>and <b>AssetModel </b>detected by the system and it’s active.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/6/63/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport4.png\" title=\"/file/images/6/63/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport4.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport4.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/6/63/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport4.png\" height=\"573\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport4_0f6ec968.png\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 573px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"800\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Close the <strong>Manage relationships</strong> window opened in the previous step.<br/>\n\tBased on the relationship between <b>Device </b>and <strong>AssetModel</strong>, now, we can show the display name of <strong>AssetModel </strong>in the report:<br/>\n\tSelect the entire table. You can see the focus indicators when the whole table is selected. <br/>\n\tExpand the AssetModel file, and then select the <strong>DisplayLabel </strong>field. Now the display name of <strong>AssetModel</strong> is shown in the table.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/4/49/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport5.png\" title=\"/file/images/4/49/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport5.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport5.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/49/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport5.png\" height=\"265\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport5_abb8eafd.png\" style=\"width:600px;height:265px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"600\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Because we already have the display name of <strong>AssetModel </strong>in the table, we can now remove the <strong>AssetModel </strong>column (<strong>Id </strong>of <strong>Asset Model</strong>) from the table by unchecking the <strong>AssetModel </strong>field under the <b>Device </b>file.<br/>\n\tAfter this, the table is shown as below:<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/0/0c/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport6.png\" title=\"/file/images/0/0c/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport6.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport6.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/0/0c/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport6.png\" height=\"321\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport6_20ed1f58.png\" style=\"width:580px;height:321px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"580\"/> </a></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Create the report</h3>\n<p>Next, we can convert the data of the table above into a clustered bar chart report:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Select the entire table. You can see the focus indicators when the whole table is selected. Then, select <strong>Clustered bar chart</strong> under the <strong>Visualizations </strong>panel.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/0/0e/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport7.png\" title=\"/file/images/0/0e/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport7.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport7.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/0/0e/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport7.png\" height=\"342\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport7_67e6a323.png\" style=\"width:200px;height:342px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"200\"/> </a><br/>\n\tNow, the table is converted into a bar chart.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/f/fc/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport8.png\" title=\"/file/images/f/fc/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport8.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport8.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/f/fc/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport8.png\" height=\"393\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport8_666d2aae.png\" style=\"width:650px;height:393px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"650\"/> </a></li>\n<li>You may notice that some of the labels on the chart aren't clear or easy to understand. You can rename them in the <strong>Visualizations</strong> panel:<br/>\n\tClick <strong>Sum of LifetimeUsageEmissions</strong> from <strong>X-aixs</strong>, and then select <strong>Rename for this visual</strong>. You may rename the label as <strong>MTCO2e</strong>, which is the unit of carbon emissions.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/e/ef/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport9.png\" title=\"/file/images/e/ef/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport9.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport9.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/e/ef/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport9.png\" height=\"800\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport9_88e7bcdd.png\" style=\"width: 611.397px; height: 800px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"611.3966480446927\"/> </a></li>\n<li>In the <strong>Visualizations </strong>panel, switch to <strong>Format your visual</strong>. Expand <strong>Title </strong>under the <strong>General </strong>tab, and then set the <strong>Text </strong>field to <strong>Hardware usage emissions by asset model</strong>.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/b/b0/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport10.png\" title=\"/file/images/b/b0/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport10.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport10.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/b/b0/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport10.png\" height=\"800\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport10_642ff7e3.png\" style=\"width: 313.48px; height: 800px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"313.4796238244514\"/> </a></li>\n<li>Now, the chart is shown like below.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/6/6b/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport11.png\" title=\"/file/images/6/6b/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport11.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport11.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/6/6b/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport11.png\" height=\"392\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport11_68a9d488.png\" style=\"width:700px;height:392px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"700\"/> </a></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Refresh the data</h3>\n<p>When the data is updated in Service Management, you need to refresh the data in Power BI to synchronize the changes.</p>\n<p>For each file, select <strong>More options</strong> and then select <strong>Refresh data</strong>. The chart will be refreshed accordingly.</p>\n<div><a class=\"image\" href=\"/file/images/9/97/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport12.png\" title=\"/file/images/9/97/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport12.png\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCarbonReport12.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/9/97/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport12.png\" height=\"800\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCarbonReport12_c42f2da1.png\" style=\"width: 608.183px; height: 800px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"608.1826831588962\"/> </a></div>\n<p><br/>\n </p>\n<div></div>\n<p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div>",
